node.text:
Why network marketing? 

The world. I’m six words into typing this caption and I’m getting emotional thinking about it.

How could you not want to see the world? Of course I wanted to. But I was a girl that grew up in a small town with nothing extra.

In a way I have very typical American history. I have a ton of European blood. Mostly Norwegian, Irish, and British. However, you can also throw in German, Ashkenazi Jew, French, Sardinian, and Iberian in the mix. 😆 You all know I’m Hawaiian, and I’m pretty sure you all know I’m Chinese. 

There’s a point to me mentioning all these places. 

No one in my family has gone back.

Financially, no one has had the opportunity to go see literally where our ancestors are from. The homes they lived in, the farms they took care of and the land they lived off of, the places my blood is buried.

I have. I almost have 1,000,000 miles on American Airlines alone. I’m extremely blessed and thankful to have business in 28 countries. I do more translated calls a week than calls in English.

The world is big. The world is beautiful. The different cultures are unbelievable. I truly believe that there is so much hate in this world because people don’t understand each other. You will if you have the opportunity to travel. You will if you break bread with people from different countries with people that look nothing like you. You will if you will open your ears and your heart to the human experience. 

Why network marketing? Because not for one single mile of those 1 million did I ever have to ask a boss if I could see where generations upon generations before me that made my life possible called home.

#bosslee

node.text:
A couple of years ago I read something on the Internet that said “imagine if everybody was as good of a human as their dogs think they are”. 

And maybe this sounds a little bit crazy but as soon as I read it I thought to myself that’s perfect. How can I make my character even better?

It is difficult to love without expectations. It is difficult to be kind to others all the time. It is hard to not judge people. It’s even harder to forgive. 

But every so often when I look at these little faces that I get to call mine I think about it. Can I be more loyal? Can I be more grateful for a little things? Can I greet everybody with a smile instead of judgment? Can I forgive past transgressions? Can I be excited to see people no matter how long it’s been? 

Of course. Be more like dogs. 

Are you more of a dog person or cat person? Comment below.

#bosslee

node.text:
Most of you don’t know this but my life started getting pretty shaky right around now four years ago.

It was my big fall from grace. 

My following was about 2% at best of what it is today and so I know a lot of you didn’t go through the darkness with me which reminds me of just how important it is to share that stage of my life.

At the time I was part of @johncmaxwell faculty trainers… at the time I was making $200,000 a month. I can also admit, at the time I was just about as egotistical as humanly possible for me.

I don’t know if you’ve ever been through a stage in your life where everything is painful. Where you are so out of alignment that your physical body hurts even deep in your chest. Where you feel like you can’t even take a deep breath you’re nearly suffocating.

That was my 2017. It was like waves crashing over me day after day. Hour after hour. I couldn’t do anything right. I felt like I was gasping for something. For anything. For just a moment of light, even. 

But it wasn’t coming. It just kept getting worse. It just kept getting darker.

And upon utter devastation there is only one thing to do. Rise like a phoenix. And that’s exactly what if you’ve known me for four years or less you’ve seen me do.

I hope things never get as dark for you as they did for me. But if you are living anywhere in the darkness let me be the one that let’s you know you too can rise.

Tag someone below who needed to read this. And drop a heart ❤️ if you resonate with it.

node.text:
Day 10. I don’t know if anything’s changed actually in my body but sheeeeesshhh I FEEL so much better energetically when I’m at the gym moving my body. 

Some super incredible man told me to start reading from a particular leadership guru and I’ve been devouring. 

I’m watching myself level up in so many ways personally and professionally from it and my trainings are getting INSANELY GOOD.

Make sure you listen to my podcast (the people’s mentor) because the episodes keep getting better and better. 

Anyway, today I was training on a call about character. And I just wanna remind all of you that character is always being developed. Are you having the courageous conversations you know you need to have? Are you living honestly? Are you living in integrity? Are you showing up as a better version of yourself every day?

I’m not asking any of that to make you feel bad about yourself. I’m asking it so you can have an awareness around becoming the person you and your loved ones deserve. ❤️❤️🥰🥰

Not only should you be a good human but you should become a better human every day. If you agree with that drop me a heart below ❤️

#bosslee

node.text:
I have to change the oddly negative connotation of network marketing faster. We have to do better faster as a profession. 

I say that because I’m listening again to one of my favorite financial mentors - like I’ve relapsed LOL - he hates network marketing and I know it’s because he doesn’t understand. And we used to talk 🤣🤣 and have even met 🤦🏻‍♀️🤦🏻‍♀️ and he’s featured again on one of my favorite podcasts and now I’m down a 4 hour rabbit hole and it’s only 9:30 am HAHHAHAHAHA 😣😭

I say this with this photo because he’s talking about living a rich life. He’s talking about going all the way in on what you love and “cutting back mercilessly” on what you don’t. 

He asked the host what his biggest money dial is and he said travel (I did too). And he said to take that and 10x what you spend on it. Something DRAMATIC and imagine what your travel looks like if you were to do that (doesn’t have to be travel. What would yours be??).

Then on another episode (cause remember I have relapsed I cannot stop) he is talking about discussing money and your DREAM RICH LIFE with your partner. I’m essentially foaming at the mouth hahhaahaa.

He said something like “Don’t let $100 a month at target ruin your entire marriage” start communicating. 

I GOTTA GO WORKOUT NOW I HAVE TO RECOVER FROM THIS BINGE LISTENING (and probably dm him and be like bruh, you trying to be on the people’s mentor podcast OR WHAT!!!!!????) 

Should I dm him? Comment yes below if you think I should reestablish this relationship 🤣🤣

Lamborghini for your attention Bc I am a bad B and I love this damn car. TURN UP THE MONEY DIAL ON EXOTICS. 

#bosslee #jessielee

node.text:
How’d it happen? How does life change so quickly but also take so long sometimes? 

Tiny habits.

One step at a time. Intentional actions. Realistic goals. One step. 

It was supposed to be $300 a month. I felt like I could do that. 

Then it turned into what if it’s $1,000 a month? What if it’s $5,000? What if it’s $500,000? What if I break the all time network marketing record?

Borrow belief from people who tell you they see something in you when you’re down. 

Collaborate and learn from people who have different gifts and skill sets, and grow. A tiny bit. Every day a tiny bit. A tiny habit. Until your life becomes unrecognizable.

If this makes sense to you drop me a heart ❤️ below

#bosslee 
#jessielee
